data.title: The Neighborhood Season 6: See what we know about release date, time, filming, where to watch, cast and more
data.meta_description: CBS announces The Neighborhood season 6 return on February 12, 2024. The 10-episode season, reduced from 22, resumes filming in December 2023. Main cast members, including Cedric the Entertainer, are expected to return for the comedy.
data.text:
Synopsis

CBS announces The Neighborhood season 6 return on February 12, 2024. The 10-episode season, reduced from 22, resumes filming in December 2023. Main cast members, including Cedric the Entertainer, are expected to return for the comedy.

The Neighborhood season 6, created by Jim Reynolds, is set to return on Monday, February 12, 2024, at 8 p.m. ET on CBS. Executive producers include Jim Reynolds, Cedric the Entertainer, Eric C. Rhone, Aaron Kaplan, Wendi Trilling, Dana Honor, Meg DeLoatch, Bill Martin, and Mike Schiff. The season will consist of 10 episodes, a departure from the usual 22.

The Neighborhood Season 6: Where to Watch?

Originally slated for a fall 2023 release, the show faced delays due to Hollywood strikes, shifting it to the midseason schedule. The fans can stream episodes on Paramount+ the day after they air on CBS.

The Neighborhood Season 6: Filming

The fifth season's last episode aired in May 2023, with confirmation of a new season received in January 2023. The start of the filming for the movie may begin in early December 2023.

The Neighborhood Season 6: Cast

The main cast, including Cedric the Entertainer, Max Greenfield, Tichina Arnold, Beth Behrs, Sheaun McKinney, Marcel Spears, and Hank Greenspan, is expected to return. Cedric the Entertainer, known for his versatile talents in acting, stand-up comedy, hosting, producing, and voice acting, adds to the show's dynamic ensemble.

For fans eager to catch up, all five seasons of The Neighborhood are currently available on Paramount+.

FAQs:

When does The Neighborhood season 6 premiere, and where can I watch it?

The Neighborhood Season 6 premieres on Monday, February 12, 2024, at 8 p.m. ET on CBS. Episodes will be available for streaming on Paramount+ the next day.

Why is The Neighborhood season 6 shorter than previous seasons?

Due to industry strikes, The Neighborhood season 6 will have only 10 episodes, a reduction from the usual 22. The filming resumes in early December 2023.
